description:
For one of the main online comparison companies in Italy, Jefferson Frank is proudly looking for a Machine Learning Engineer.

The client has offices in Milan and Pavia, and offers the chance to work from home as well - although presence on-site will be required at least once per week.

Salary up to € 45.000 - please note only candidates with at least 3 years working experience or equivalent PhD experience will be considered for this role.

Required Skills

at least a bachelor degree in computer science, math or other STEM subjects;
3 years experience on hands-on ML/DL projects;
broad knowledge of Python and its data science/machine learning frameworks (scikit-learn, pandas, numpy..);
experience with relational databases;
previous experience on Linux;
ability and confidence in communicating with non-technical audience and other parts of the business;
ability to work autonomously and within deadlines.

Please note this is not a full remote role, and you need to able to legally work in Europe in order to apply (you are the holder of a EU Passport or you are the holder of EU residency permit or you are the holder of a Schengen Work Visa).

Jefferson Frank is the Amazon Web Services (AWS) recruiter of choice. We work with organizations worldwide to find and deliver the best permanent and contract AWS DevOps, Big Data, Data Science, IaaS and PaaS, and AWS Security professionals on the planet.

For more information, visit jeffersonfrank.com.
